  <h2>The Commercial Launch</h2>

  <p>PhilWeb Corp. and Tiger Resort, Leisure and Entertainment Inc. have officially launched Okada Play, an online gaming platform that brings the Okada Manila integrated resort brand into the Philippine digital gaming market. The commercial launch, confirmed through a joint announcement by both companies, represents a significant milestone in the convergence of land-based and online gaming in the Philippines.</p>

  <p>The partnership agreement was signed by Nobuki Sato, Chief Operating Officer of Okada Manila, and Brian Ng, President of PhilWeb Corp., in a ceremony held at the Okada Manila property in Paranaque City. The signing formalized a development relationship that had been in progress for over a year, with Okada Play undergoing private beta testing with a limited player pool since early 2026.</p>

  <p>"Okada Play is not simply an online casino attached to a resort name," Sato said during the launch event. "It is an extension of the experience that Okada Manila delivers on property. Our guests expect seamlessness, and this platform delivers it across channels."</p>

  <h2>The PhilWeb Technology Stack</h2>

  <p>Okada Play is powered by PhilWeb Corp.'s Online Gaming Platform (OGP) solution, a proprietary technology stack that PhilWeb has developed and refined over two decades in the Philippine gaming technology market. The OGP provides a full suite of capabilities: gaming content aggregation from over 40 licensed content suppliers, scalable cloud infrastructure, real-time analytics, payment processing (including GCash, Maya, and bank transfer integration), KYC/AML compliance modules, and 24/7 customer service support.</p>

  <p>Brian Ng described the OGP as "the most battle-tested gaming platform in the Philippine market," noting that PhilWeb currently operates or licenses its technology to multiple PAGCOR-licensed gaming operators. "What makes the Okada Play deployment unique is the depth of the brand integration," Ng said. "We've built custom interfaces, VIP tier logic, and loyalty point conversion that connects directly to Okada Manila's on-property systems."</p>

  <div class="pull-quote">
    <p>"Okada Play is not simply an online casino attached to a resort name. It is an extension of the experience that Okada Manila delivers on property."</p>
    <cite>Nobuki Sato, COO, Okada Manila</cite>
  </div>

  <h2>The Omnichannel Strategy</h2>

  <p>The launch of Okada Play is described by both companies as a central pillar of Okada Manila's broader digital transformation strategy. The concept of "omnichannel gaming," borrowed from the retail industry, refers to the seamless integration of physical and digital touchpoints. For Okada Manila, this means that a guest who plays at a baccarat table on the casino floor can continue playing from the same account on Okada Play after returning home, with loyalty points, VIP tier status, and promotional offers carrying across both channels.</p>

  <p>This approach mirrors strategies that have been deployed by major operators in Las Vegas (notably MGM's BetMGM and Caesars Digital) and Macau (Sands China's digital loyalty programs). In the Philippine context, however, Okada Play represents one of the first attempts to implement a true omnichannel strategy by a major integrated resort.</p>

